From: Florent Revest <revestflo@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 4 Jun 2026 14:30:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Wait for FunctionFS FFS_ACTIVE before configfs_set_udc

Upstream-Status: Inappropriate [aurora-specific workaround]

Aurora ships an adb_mode that uses a FunctionFS function (ffs.adb).
The kernel composite_bind() walk calls ffs_func_bind() which requires
the FunctionFS instance to be in FFS_ACTIVE state (raw_descs_data and
raw_descs_length set, see drivers/usb/gadget/function/f_fs.c) -- if
not, it returns -ENODEV, composite_bind fails, the UDC write returns
ENODEV.

usb-moded's appsync_activate_pre() calls systemd's StartUnit() (the
D-Bus reply returns as soon as the job is queued, NOT when the unit
reaches Active state) and then immediately calls
appsync_mark_active_locked() on the app. By the time
modesetting_enter_dynamic_mode falls through to configfs_set_udc(),
the corresponding adbd hasn't opened /dev/usb-ffs/adb/ep0 yet, let
alone written the function descriptors.

The wait MUST happen AFTER configfs_set_function() (which creates the
configfs functions/ffs.adb dir adbd-prepare needs to mount FunctionFS
against) and BEFORE configfs_set_udc(): adbd-prepare's mount only
succeeds once that configfs function dir exists, then adbd's ep0 open
+ descriptor write triggers FFS_ACTIVE which makes ep1 appear, and
only THEN can the UDC write succeed.

This is a hack and not the right long-term fix (that would be to make
appsync_mark_active_locked actually wait for systemd's JobRemoved or
poll the unit's ActiveState property). But it unblocks aurora rootfs
adb with the minimum diff.

Hardcoded for ffs.adb because that's the only FunctionFS function
aurora ships in dyn-modes. A generic implementation would iterate
over all configs/b.1/ffs.* symlinks; happy to refactor on request.
---
 src/usb_moded-modesetting.c | 18 ++++++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 18 insertions(+)

--- a/src/usb_moded-modesetting.c
+++ b/src/usb_moded-modesetting.c
@@ -769,6 +769,24 @@
         char *id = config_get_android_vendor_id();
         configfs_set_vendorid(data->idVendorOverride ?: id);
         free(id);
+        /* HACK: ffs_func_bind() in kernel composite_bind requires the
+         * FunctionFS instance in FFS_ACTIVE state -- i.e. adbd must
+         * have already opened ep0 and written descriptors. Otherwise
+         * the UDC write below returns ENODEV and we fall through to
+         * charging_only. Poll for ep1 (only exists after descriptors
+         * have been written) so we don't race ahead of adbd. This must
+         * sit AFTER configfs_set_function() (which mkdir'd functions/
+         * ffs.adb so adbd-prepare's `mount -t functionfs adb` can find
+         * the kernel-side instance) and BEFORE configfs_set_udc().
+         */
+        const char *ffs_ep1 = "/dev/usb-ffs/adb/ep1";
+        for( int i = 0; i < 60; ++i ) {
+            if( access(ffs_ep1, F_OK) == 0 ) {
+                log_debug("FunctionFS ready (%s present)", ffs_ep1);
+                break;
+            }
+            g_usleep(500 * 1000);
+        }
         if( !configfs_set_udc(true) )
             goto EXIT;
     }
